The more you drag your mouse outward, the larger the star will be, and the other way around. Don't take too much time perfecting the size, but make sure it is easy to manipulate. As you form the desired polygon, two small white squares appear on an inner point and an outer point. This is to make the shape of the star. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pulling the outer square out will result in a thinner, longer pointed star, while pulling inward will make a smaller, stouter star. Pulling the inner square out will make the star bigger and wider, possibly turning it into a pentagon. Pushing it in will make the star thinner overall, so be careful when using it. Decide your final shape. Again, as long as the size is easy to use, go with it; you don't need to be exact. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/19/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/19/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

See all of the type-in boxes? This will adjust the different qualities of the stars. Explanations of the different things in this:

The two shapes{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6e\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6e\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

There is a 5 pointed star, and a pentagon. Simply put, the pentagon is for making a polygon, and the star for, well, a star! {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/b0\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/b0\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Corners{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a9\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a9\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


For Polygon:
This is for the amount of points/corners in the shape. You can make a triangle with 3, square with 4, pentagon with 5, etc...{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/19\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet5.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/19\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet5.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


For Star:
This is the amount of extending points in the star. 3 for three pointed, 4 for 4 pointed, 5 for 5 pointed, etc... Also, there is an unlimited amount of corners you can do, though it starts getting too circular as it increases too much. Note: There is no 2 because it is impossible to make a plane figure with less than 3 sides. Spoke Ratio{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/ea\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet9.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet9.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/ea\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet9.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

This basically shows how wide/thin the sides and middle will be. the higher the ratio, the wider the star/polygon will be. It gets thinner as it lowers. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d4\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet10.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet10.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d4\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet10.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet10.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

The maximum ratio is 1 ( a star turns into a polygon), and the minimum is .010 (Quite thin)

Rounded{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/b7\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet12.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet12.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/b7\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet12.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet12.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

This is used to make rounded segments in the star/polygon (or just rounds the point); the larger number, the larger the shape will be, it also goes into negatives, where it goes the opposite direction. This goes into many various forms and changes as the other parts of the shape change(corner, spoke ratio, etc...). This is the most important component in making a mandala. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e3\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet13.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet13.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e3\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet13.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet13.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Note: The more corners you add to the mandala, the more sophisticated everything will look. Randomized{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ca\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet15.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet15.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ca\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet15.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet15.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

This makes the shape asymmetrical. It is not recommended you use this part when making a mandala, as it is important to make it as geometrical as possible. You can save the randomization tool for making abstract art. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a8\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet16.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet16.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a8\/Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet16.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Mandala-in-Inkscape-Step-5Bullet16.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Experiment with these! Testing out the buttons may not be a good thing to do in this case of picking between a green and a red button, but it is perfect to do it in this case! Once you get the hang of it, manipulating the shape will be much easier. Try making a file specifically used for making test designs, that way, you can save much more room, and record data for next time if needed.

